'''Yvon Landry Mvogo Nganoma''' (born 6 June 1994) is a Swiss professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{French football updater|Lorient}} club [[FC Lorient|Lorient]]. Born in Cameroon, he plays for the [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland national team]].

==Club career==
Mvogo was born in [[Yaoundé]], Cameroon.<ref name=":0" /> He made his professional debut at 17 August 2013 in the [[Swiss Cup]] against Veyrier. He played the full game in an 8-0 away win. He wears kit number 18. His contract expires in June 2018.<ref name=":0">{{cite web |title=Switzerland - Y. Mvogo |url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/yvon-landry--mvogo/182815/ |website=Soccerway |access-date=2 September 2021}}</ref>{{citation needed|date=January 2025}}

In April 2017, it was revealed that Mvogo will be joining [[Bundesliga]] and future [[2017–18 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League]] debutants [[RasenBallsport Leipzig|Leipzig]] on 1 July 2017, after signing a four-year deal with the [[Saxony]]-based club.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.dierotenbullen.com/neuigkeiten/Saison_2016_17/Neuzugang-Yvon-Mvogo.html/ |title=22-JÄHRIGER KOMMT IM SOMMER VOM SCHWEIZER ERSTLIGISTEN YOUNG BOYS BERN - VIERJAHRESVERTRAG BIS 2021 - BEREITS 25 EUROPAPOKALSPIELE |access-date=8 May 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170417132504/http://www.dierotenbullen.com/neuigkeiten/Saison_2016_17/Neuzugang-Yvon-Mvogo.html |archive-date=17 April 2017 |language=de |url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 25 August 2020, Mvogo signed for [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] on a two-year loan.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Official: Yvon Mvogo joins PSV on loan|url=https://bulinews.com/news/5838/official-yvon-mvogo-joins-psv-loan|access-date=25 August 2020|website=Bulinews|date=25 August 2020 |language=en}}</ref> On 14 July 2022, he signed a two-year contract with [[FC Lorient|Lorient]] in France.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Lorient|url=https://fclweb.fr/yvon-mvogo-signe-au-fc-lorient/|title=YVON MVOGO SIGNE AU FC LORIENT|date=13 July 2022|access-date=13 July 2022|language=fr}}</ref>

==International career==
Mvogo got his first call up to the [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland senior national team]] squad for a [[UEFA Euro 2016]] qualifier against [[Lithuania national football team|Lithuania]] in June 2015.<ref>{{cite web |title=Lithuania vs Switzerland (1-2) Jun 14, 2015 Match Stats |url=https://www.footballcritic.com/uefa-euro-qualification-lithuania-switzerland/match-stats/387540 |website=FootballCritic |access-date=2 September 2021}}</ref> He was included in Switzerland's 23-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Switzerland opts for experience in World Cup squad |url=https://apnews.com/article/b886bdc694bf4942a35f1dcfd01c2697 |access-date=2 September 2021 |work=Associated Press News |date=4 June 2018}}</ref> He made his first appearance for the national team on 15 October 2018 against [[Iceland national football team|Iceland]] for a [[2018–19 UEFA Nations League]] group match.

In May 2019, he was named to the national team for the [[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals]], but did not play in either of Switzerland's matches as his side finished fourth.<ref>{{cite news |last1=McNulty |first1=Phil |title=Nations League: England beat Switzerland 6-5 on penalties after 0-0 draw |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/48191915 |access-date=2 September 2021 |work=BBC Sport |date=9 June 2019}}</ref> In 2021 he was called up to the national team for the [[UEFA European Championship|2020 UEFA European Championship]], where the team created one of the main sensations of the tournament reaching the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite web |title=Switzerland-Spain - UEFA EURO 2020 |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro-2020/match/2024485--switzerland-vs-spain/ |website=UEFA |access-date=2 September 2021}}{{dead link|date=March 2025|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>

Mvogo returned to the Switzerland national team in September 2023 and played during a pair of matches against [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]] and [[Romania national football team|Romania]] during [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying|UEFA Euro 2024 qualification]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Yvon Mvogo |url=https://www.national-football-teams.com/player/72261/Yvon_Mvogo.html |website=National Football Teams}}</ref>

